				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=1383">Eruds Crossing</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Vambraces of Ro</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Vambraces of Ro</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=69690"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:kyle@en.com">Salthorn</a> | 
		                        1/20/2000 7:18:31 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">For the vambraces of ro, one needs to<BR>
obtain two rotten shark portions.  I <BR>
know from other spoiler sites that the<BR>
plague shark (level 30 or so)is a rarish <BR>
spawn in Erud's Crossing.  However, there <BR>
are also Killer Sharks (around level 40)<BR>
that also cruise the area.  I have been<BR>
told that the plague shark spawns around<BR>
the sunken ship, northwest of Erud's<BR>
Crossing, but is frequently killed by <BR>
the high level sharks.  I was hoping to <BR>
get information to find out if these tips<BR>
are true and also to obtain general <BR>
information regarding tips as to how best<BR>
do this quest.  This is particularly <BR>
difficult since you have to obtain two<BR>
rotten shark portions.  Any help will be <BR>
appreciated.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
