	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Looking around on the web and comparing other people's findings to my own, it seems maybe Verant has fixed some of the behavior of the Plague Shark and so the process needs a new explanation.<BR>
<BR>
To do the job right, you'll need a balanced group: a tracker (Ranger or Druid), a Paladin (who's quest is this anyway?), a dedicated nuker (mage or wiz), and another body just to help pick up the damage the shark deals, preferrably a tank or a healer. Make sure that at least one of the people in the party can cast enduring breath or can summon water stones. There should be 4 people in the party all above level 30.<BR>
<BR>
Go to Qeynos or Erudin and catch the boat that takes you to Erud's Crossing. When the boat zones to Erud's Crossing, you will see an island. When coming from Qeynos, the boat will stop at the dock. If coming from Erudin, you will need to jump off the boat and swim to the island. There are allegedly Killer Sharks in the zone, but I've looked for them and still couldn't find them. There are lots of &quot;a shark&quot; swimming around. They con green at level 33 and never once tried to attack me, even as I swam in their midst. By the way, you're going to an island with cats, but not &quot;Cat Island&quot;. There is only one island in Erud's crossing, I believe it's called Kerra Island.<BR>
<BR>
When you're standing on the dock, face the ocean so that the island is to your back. Now turn 90 degrees left and walk past the pair of cat-people standing on the beach and keep walking until you see a solitary cat standing on his own little piece of dirt right on the beach. It's about half way between the dock and the sunken ship that sticks out of the water. From what I can tell, the Plague Shark seems to spawn on the ocean floor below this cat you're standing next to. Your tracker will be able to further narrow down the shark's position. Here's another helpful tip; when the tracker starts tracking the shark, swim in the water so that you are always against the ocean floor. The shark is never near the top or even halfway, he's always on the ocean floor from what I saw.<BR>
<BR>
You must fight the shark where you find him. This is why everybody needs enduring breath. I never saw the shark follow anybody towards the top of the water, he instead aggros on somebody else nearby. The fighters will taunt and slash, nukers nuke, the shark goes down pretty quickly.<BR>
<BR>
It used to be reported that the shark was tethered to a ship called the Seaking and could be found as the ship zoned in. I never saw this. It also used to be reported that the shark would &quot;shadow step&quot; as you fought him. I never saw this either. Instead, the shark will automatically cast an effect that makes &quot;your body hurt as your mind clears&quot;. Whatever this is, it takes lots of hitpoints fast. The nuker needs to kill this thing pronto.<BR>
<BR>
Loot the body. The body of the shark doesn't always drop the prize. In this case, you will need to start the process over again. Based on my experience, the shark spawns every two hours and has no place holders. There is nothing else interesting to do on this island, so I suggest that everybody camp their respective characters and play those alternates you've been neglecting or go rent a copy of &quot;Big Trouble in Little China&quot;. What a great movie. After two hours, the shark is back and you should all try again. Good luck!<BR>
<BR>
One last note; the shark once beached itsself next to the dock. As the tanks swam to it, we couldn't hit it due to some bug in the game. And as the nukers cast spells on it, they couldn't hit it either. BUT, if the tanks engaged in melee (still not hitting it, but getting hit themselves), then the nukers could hit it. At the end, I was still able to loot the shark and got what I needed. Be prepared for that eventuality. It could happen again.<BR>
<BR>
Good luck to all you Paladins out there!<BR>
<BR>
Looseal Lawful<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
