	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				After the patch on 4.12.2k the plague shark will spawn as the boat the 'Seaking'(click on the boat and you get the name) comes into the dock at Erud's Crossing. If you stand to the north a little ways(not much though) of the 2 cats that are north of the dock, the plague shark will be right in front of you, to the east, a little ways. You do not have to swim past the track the boat follows as it docks to get to the plague shark. They seem to spawn one at a time. The Seaking comes in on a cycle of 20-22 minutes. The plague sharks con red to me, 28 Ranger, and blue to a 35 Paladin. We couldn't kill it with just the 2 of us. We had to enlist the help of some higher levels that were hunting killer sharks. They hit as high as 77pts and are quite fast. They do cast as well. I never once saw a plague shark by the sunken ship. I timed this for over 4 hours on 4.12.2k, and like clockwork, if you see the 'Seaking', you will find a plague shark to north of the dock. The plague shark does seem to be caught in a pathing loop in this area, so the location or pathing might change in a future patch.<BR>
<BR>
Giljorak Ryvanshire &lt;Blood Circle&gt;<BR>
Ranger of the 28th Season<BR>
Prexus 
				</font>
